95
00:06:10,796 --> 00:06:13,292
That was for me.
Not her.

96
00:06:13,292 --> 00:06:14,518
I had dark days.

97
00:06:14,518 --> 00:06:18,234
And your flimsy intruder story?

98
00:06:18,316 --> 00:06:21,815
If I were a liar, I would've
thought of something better.

99
00:06:23,187 --> 00:06:25,378
Recognize this ring?

100
00:06:28,737 --> 00:06:31,547
Lindsay gave it to me
when I graduated med shcool.

101
00:06:31,547 --> 00:06:33,736
How did you get it?

102
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:36,901
Tell us about the patient you lost.

103
00:06:37,573 --> 00:06:39,663
Alan?

104
00:06:39,992 --> 00:06:43,031
He and Diane were our
best friends.

105
00:06:43,031 --> 00:06:46,263
I made this mistake and it
changed course of all our lives.

106
00:06:46,263 --> 00:06:49,029
Especially when Diane sued you.

107
00:06:49,202 --> 00:06:51,477
I couldn't face her.

108
00:06:51,588 --> 00:06:53,527
I..

109
00:06:53,527 --> 00:06:55,533
shrank.

110
00:06:55,533 --> 00:06:58,274
